---------------------------------
-- P4A - PHP For Applications. --
---------------------------------

-----------
-- Setup --
-----------

Just extract the archive under your web server
DOCUMENT_ROOT (es:/home/httpd/htdocs).

You should rename the directory
"p4a-version" to "p4a".

If you want to see the sample project than you
must install the database with this commands
(as root/administrator):

	cd /home/httpd/htdocs/p4a
	cd projects/sample
	mysql < sample.sql
	
than open browser and go to:

	http://localhost/p4a/
	
the sample project will start by default.

-------------------
-- Documentation --
-------------------

All p4a documentation is in "/docs"
directory under p4a installation.

------------------------------------
-- P4A compatibility: Server Side --
------------------------------------

Linux/Windows
Apache 1.3.x/2.0.x
php/mod_php 4.3.x
	
------------------------------------------------
-- P4A compatibility: Workstation Side --
------------------------------------------------

Gecko browsers (Mozilla 1.x, Netscape 6.x, 7.x)
Internet Explorer 5.x, 6.x
Safari 1.x
Opera 6.x, 7.x
Konqueror 3.x
Any JavaScript 1.2 browser with css/css2 support

Nescape 4.x is not supported

-------------------------------------------
-- P4A compatibility: Mobile Side --
-------------------------------------------

coming soon.

-------------------
-- General Notes --
-------------------

P4A automatically disable magic_quotes_runtime
and magic_quotes_sybase, setting their value to the
PHP default.
magic_quotes_gpc must be Off (PHP default).

You can't switch between two project with the same
P4A_PROJECT_NAME under the same virtual host
without closing the browser.

-----------------------------------------------
-- Rich text editing and spell checker notes --
-----------------------------------------------

To enable spell checking feature on rich editors,
remember that you must have perl executable with
these modules:

	Text::Aspell
	XML::DOM
	CGI
	
Of these, only Text::Aspell might need to be 
installed manually. The others are likely to 
be available by default in most Perl distributions.

You must also set executable this file:
themes/default/widgets/rich_textarea/plugins/SpellChecker/spell-check-logic.cgi

Because of UFT-8, you should have perl 5.8 installed or,
at least perl 5.6.1.

--------------------
-- Notes on Opera --
--------------------

P4A default theme does not seem to be
compatible with Opera, because of the heavy
CSS2 utilization.
Maybe there will be a simpler theme for all
browser that cannot support CSS2.

P4A fields use "div" tags for a nice
alignment, Opera does not seem to understand this
structure and...

P4A default menu ("drop_down") 
will not run on Opera 6.x, but only on Opera 7.x.
If Opera 7.x cannot be installed than use differt menu
style such as "tabbed" or "tabbed_rounded".

